		<OtherText>
			<TextTypeCode>04</TextTypeCode>
			<Text>Struggling with depression can feel like an unending battle."ACTion for Depression" offers new way forward, combining the science of Acceptance and Commitment Therapy (ACT) with compassionate, real-world guidance. This book provides a roadmap for those seeking to understand and manage depression, focusing on acceptance, mindfulness, and values-based action. Whether you're a counsellor, a mental health professional, a person living with depression, or someone who supports a loved one, this book will empower you with practical tools to move beyond the struggle and build a life of meaning and fulfilment. Through clear explanations, relatable examples, and actionable exercises, "ACTion for Depression" will help you take the first steps toward accepting and rediscover a life worth living.</Text>
